%N A093070 Decimal expansion of 128/(45*Pi).
%C A093070 Average length of a line picked at random in a unit disk.
%C A093070 This average was apparently first calculated by the Austrian mathematician Emanuel Czuber (1851-1925) in 1884. - _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 26 2026
%H A093070 Emanuel Czuber, <a href="https://archive.org/details/geometwahrschein00czubrich/page/n208/mode/1up">Geometrische Wahrscheinlichkeiten und Mittelwerte</a>, Leipzig, B. G. Teubner, 1884, p. 204.
%H A093070 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CircularSectorLinePicking.html">Circular Sector Line Picking</a>.
%H A093070 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/DiskLinePicking.html">Disk Line Picking</a>.
%H A093070 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A093070 Equals (256*A086201)/45. - _Kritsada Moomuang_, Sep 19 2020
%e A093070 0.90541478736722679904076096496363725957381487354570...
